HEADWORD: Veneering
<hw>Ve*neer"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of
one who veneers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Thin wood or other material used as a
veneer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Venefical</ent>⟦br⟧
